HEADWORD: Chiffon
<hw>Chif`fon"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., lit., rag.
See <er>Chiffonier</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Any merely ornamental
adjunct of a woman's dress, as a bunch of ribbon, lace, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of soft gauzy material used for ruches,
trimmings, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chiffonier</ent>⟦br⟧
